transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I got... I had a prescription sent to me and...

Speaker 1: Which, you know, was a little strange because I didn't put an auto refill.

Speaker 2: But anyways, it was basically just an empty bag.

Speaker 1: There was a hole in the bag and the prescription was not there.

Speaker 2: What was your first and last name, sir?

Speaker 1: Don Fuller, F-U-L-L-E-R.

Speaker 2: And did you get any sort of, like, notification from USPS or anything like that, Mr. Fuller?

Speaker 1: No. Nope.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay, no worries.

Speaker 1: Usually, we'd have you, like, file a claim, you know, and depending on the terms of the investigation,

Speaker 2: we'd either reship or take whatever appropriate action.

Speaker 1: This is only your second order. You said you weren't expecting it either way.

Speaker 2: I definitely will go ahead and replace this for you at no cost.

Speaker 1: And it's been noted down here on your profile, so if anything goes missing in the future,

Speaker 2: we just make sure we take appropriate steps in order to locate it.

Speaker 1: As a one-time courtesy, no problem at all.

Speaker 2: I'm going to reship. It should have been 10 pills for you.

Speaker 1: So you'll see that come out before the end of this week, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay. So then, is there a reason why it's auto fill?

Speaker 1: Yeah, it looks like you set up on our VIP prescription to receive refills.

Speaker 2: I can pause that service for you as well if you did want to, like, receive pills in the future

Speaker 1: or, like, place orders or just keep the prescription active.

Speaker 2: You can do that manually online or over the phone.

Speaker 1: And I've looked online.

Speaker 2: Like I say, I didn't expect it to be an auto, you know, refill kind of thing

Speaker 1: because I was just trying it out.

Speaker 2: And so what I was going to do when I refilled it would go to the $100,000 or whatever,

Speaker 1: instead of the $50,000.

Speaker 2: But like I say, then they just sort of, you know, showed up.

Speaker 1: And I was like, well, you know, without anything in it.

Speaker 2: You know, I was like, well, I opened it, you know, because the side is open.

Speaker 1: And I'm like, why is there stuff for this, you know, this blue, you know?

Speaker 2: And I was like, so then I looked at my account.

Speaker 1: And it was like, oh, they shipped something a month later.

Speaker 2: So it was like, well, I didn't expect it to auto because, you know,

Speaker 1: I was basically trying it out, right?

Speaker 2: So I'd like to change it to the 100 milligrams instead of 50

Speaker 1: and the same amount of pills, but probably do like every three months.

Speaker 2: Or I don't know if I could just go in there and, you know, change the...

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can push it for you 90 days.

Speaker 2: And then what you can do is you can always call anytime in between then

Speaker 1: if you ever need it sooner or if you ever need a little more time, just give us a shout.

Speaker 2: Right.

Speaker 1: Now, is there a way to get it to 100 instead of the 50?

Speaker 2: Exactly, yeah.

Speaker 1: So I'll take care of that for you as well.

Speaker 2: No issue at all.

Speaker 1: When I send this replacement order, it'll be as the 100 milligram option, not the 50.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: And still the same amount of pills, right?

Speaker 2: Yes, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: And like I say, I definitely will, you know, try to deal with the post office.

Speaker 2: You know how that goes.

Speaker 1: Yeah, absolutely, I do.

Speaker 2: No issue there.

Speaker 1: So I'm going to send you out this replacement, Mr. Fuller,

Speaker 2: so look out for that in the next few days, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, and then 30 days from basically now or whatever will be the next shipment?

Speaker 2: 90 days.

Speaker 1: 90, that's what I'm sorry.

Speaker 2: Yep, 90 days after this.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, that sounds good.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: All right, bye.
